# User Secrets Template
# Use this template to set up user secrets for development
# Run: dotnet user-secrets init (in the API project folder)
# Then run: dotnet user-secrets set "Jwt:SecretKey""YourActualSecretKeyHere"

## JWT Configuration
{
    "Jwt": {
        "SecretKey": "YourSecureSecretKeyForDevelopmentShouldBe64CharactersLong123456",
        "Issuer": "UserAuthAPI-Dev",
        "Audience": "UserAuthAPI-Dev"
    },
    "ConnectionStrings": {
        "DefaultConnection": "Data Source=userauth-dev.db"
    },
    "ExternalServices": {
        "EmailService": {
            "ApiKey": "your-email-service-api-key",
            "BaseUrl": "https://api.emailservice.com"
        }
    }
}

## Command Examples:
# dotnet user-secrets set "Jwt:SecretKey""YourActualSecretKeyHere"
# dotnet user-secrets set "ConnectionStrings:DefaultConnection""Server=localhost;Database=UserAuthDev;..."
# dotnet user-secrets set "ExternalServices:EmailService:ApiKey""your-real-api-key"